A Valiant Win for LA
data.description: With a rough start to the 2019 season, the Los Angeles Valiant know they have a tough road to make season playoffs. Custa and FCTFCTN describe how defeating the #1 Vancouver Titans and putting an end to their 19 win regular season streak will build the team’s confidence to achieve that goal.

data.title: Saebyeolbe – Back in Blue
data.description: Being benched for the New York Excelsior for most of the 2019 season, star DPS player Jong-Ryeol “Saebyeolbe” Park didn’t know when he’d see playtime again. Grinding his way on Sombra, Saebyeolbe is back to prove he’s not done yet.

data.title: Watchpoint Comms Check – Los Angeles Valiant
data.description: Struggling from a rough start to the 2019 Overwatch League season, the Los Angeles Valiant have been slowly building their way back up the league standings. Join the team comms on stage as they win over Chengdu, Shanghai, London and hand the Vancouver Titans their first regular season loss.

data.title: Los Angeles Gladiators: Flying under the Radar
data.description: Jockeying for a spot in the overall Overwatch League playoffs, the Los Angeles Gladiators have steadily won big matches but still come up short in the discourse among “teams to fear”. Surefour and Biggoose describe the Gladiators of late and what they are doing to make their mark in the 2019 season.

data.title: The Dancing Outlaw – Jake and Mica learn to Dance
data.description: Overwatch League Insider Mica Burton takes Jake of the Houston Outlaws to get professional dance lessons. Will being agile in the Overwatch League translate to being agile on the dance floor?
